title: Two-Body Photodisintegration of The Deutron From 100 To 800 Mev.

x4freetext: TWO-BODY PHOTODISINTEGRATION OF THE DEUTRON FROM 100
TO 800 MEV.

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Glasgow, Glasgow, Scotland, United Kingdom
Universita degli Studi di Pavia + INFN Pavia, Italy

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.603, p.303 (1996)

x4freetext: ELECTRON TAGGED BREMSSTRAHLUNG:  GLASGOW
TAGGED PHOTON  SPECTROMETER  INSTALLED AT THE MAMI IN
MAINZ.
MAMI MAINZ RACETRACK MICROTRON.
LIQUID  DEUTERIUM AT  24 K  AND  1153 MBAR  INSIDE THE
CRYOGENIC TARGET.
THREE  PHOTOPROTON IDENTIFICATION METHODS
HAVE BEEN DEVELOPED TO COPE VERY WIDE RENGE OF PROTON
ENERGIES  ALL  USED  THE  PROTON  ENERGY  LOSSES  AND
DEGRADATION IN DIFFERENT SCINTILLATOR LAYERS.
THE  LARGE  ACCEPTANCE  DETECTOR  DAPHNE,
DEVELOPED BY INFN, ITALY AND CEA-SPHN, SACLAY, FRANCE
DIRECT MEASUREMENT.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: STATISTICAL ERRORS ARE GIVEN. THE
SYSTEMATIC ERROR IS ESTIMATED TO BE LESS THAN 3.5 %.
THE TOTAL AND THE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS  FOR THE
REACTION D(G,P)N HAVE BEEN MEASURED OVER  THE  PHOTON
ENERGY RANGE  100  -  800  MEV  AT  THE  855 MEV MAMI
MICROTRON IN  MAINZ.  USING  THE   LARGE   ACCEPTANCE
DETECTOR DAPHNE  IN  CONJUNCTION WITH GLASGOW TAGGING
SPECTROMETER, HIGH  PRECISION  RESULTS   WITH   SMALL
SYSTEMATIC ERRORS   WERE   OBTAINED.   THE  DATA  ARE
PRESENTED IN  THE   FORM   OF   THIRTY-FIVE   ANGULAR
DISTRIBUTIONS AT C.M.  PROTON ANGLES BETWEEN 30 - 160
DEGREE IN 10 DEGREE INTERVALS AND AT PHOTON  ENERGIES
IN STEPS OF 20 MEV.
